config MCHP_XEC_CCT_KTIMER
	bool "Microchip XEC Capture Compare timer as kernel timer"
	default y
	depends on DT_HAS_MICROCHIP_XEC_CCT_KTIMER_ENABLED && !MCHP_XEC_RTOS_TIMER
	select TICKLESS_CAPABLE
	select SYSTEM_TIMER_HAS_DISABLE_SUPPORT
	# Advertise LPM-companion capability; the actual mode (HOOKS) is chosen as a
	# default of the SYSTEM_TIMER_LPM_COMPANION choice (select cannot target a
	# choice symbol). See drivers/timer/Kconfig.system_timer_lpm.
	select SYSTEM_TIMER_HAS_LPM_COMPANION_SUPPORT
	help
	  Kernel device driver for system tick with tickless capability.
	  The capture compare timer uses a 48MHz input clock with a power of 2
	  clock divider register dividing by 1 through 128. (48MHz through 375 KHz). 
	  The device has a 32-bit free run auto-wrapping counter at the selected frequency,
	  two 32-bit compare registers, and 6 32-bit capture registers. Each compare register
	  can generate a separate interrupt when the free counter matches the value in the
	  compare register. CCT requires the SoC PLL enabled. For sleep modes where the PLL
	  is turn off, this driver implements the system timer LPM companion hooks called by
	  the SoC PM code.
